в”Ӯ ## Executive Summary                                                         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The investigated Windows 10 memory image shows clear evidence of APT         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ compromise. Two suspicious processes with unusual names (`license_ctrl.e`    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ and `ftusbsrvc.exe`) were found actively listening on network ports, with    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ evidence of command and control communication to IP address 172.16.4.10 on   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ port 8080.                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Timeline of Events                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **2018-09-05 14:27:55**: ftusbsrvc.exe establishes listening port 33001    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **2018-09-06 17:17:20**: license_ctrl.e establishes listening port 5682    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **Multiple timestamps**: Connections observed to 172.16.4.10:8080          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ indicating ongoing C2 activity                                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Indicators of Compromise                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **Processes**: license_ctrl.e (PID 1716), ftusbsrvc.exe (PID 4916)         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **Network**: 172.16.4.10:8080 (C2 server), ports 5682 and 33001 (local     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ listeners)                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **Behavior**: Unusual process names with network listening capabilities    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Persistence Mechanisms                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The investigation focused on active memory analysis. Further filesystem      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ analysis would be needed to identify specific persistence mechanisms used by в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ these malicious processes.                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Recommendations                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 1. Immediately isolate the affected system from the network                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 2. Block communication to 172.16.4.10 at network perimeter                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 3. Hunt for similar process names across the environment                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 4. Conduct full disk forensics to identify persistence mechanisms            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 5. Review network logs for additional compromised systems communicating with в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 172.16.4.10                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
