в”Ӯ The Windows 10 x64 system from SRL-2018 APT hunt scenario shows clear        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ evidence of compromise with active command and control (C2) infrastructure.  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ Two malicious processes with suspicious names are running persistent         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ services, while maintaining communications with external C2 servers.         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Timeline of Events                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **2018-09-05 14:27:55**: ftusbsrvc.exe begins listening on port 33001      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **2018-09-06 17:17:20**: license_ctrl.e begins listening on port 5682      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **Multiple timestamps**: Active C2 communications to 172.16.4.10:8080      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **2018-09-06**: Peak activity with multiple connection attempts            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Indicators of Compromise                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **Processes**: license_ctrl.e (PID 1716), ftusbsrvc.exe (PID 4916)         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **Network**: Communications to 172.16.4.10:8080                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **Ports**: 5682 (license_ctrl.e), 33001 (ftusbsrvc.exe)                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **Behavior**: Non-standard process names, suspicious port usage, external  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ C2 communications                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Persistence Mechanisms                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - Both malicious processes established listening services on non-standard    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ports                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - Process names designed to masquerade as legitimate system components       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - Network infrastructure suggesting established C2 channels                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Recommendations                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 1. Immediately isolate the compromised system                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 2. Block communications to 172.16.4.10:8080                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 3. Hunt for additional systems communicating with this IP                    в”Ӯ
