в”Ӯ ## Executive Summary                                                         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The Windows 10 system has been compromised by Advanced Persistent Threat     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ (APT) actors. Two malicious processes have been identified running backdoor  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ services with active command and control communications to external          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ infrastructure.                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Timeline of Events                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **2018-09-05 14:27:55** - ftusbsrvc.exe process started, listening on port в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 33001                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **2018-09-06 17:17:20** - license_ctrl.e process started, listening on     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ port 5682                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - **Multiple instances** - Outbound connections established to               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 172.16.4.10:8080 for C2 communications                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Indicators of Compromise                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ **Malicious Processes:**                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - license_ctrl.e (PID 1716) - Backdoor listener on port 5682                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - ftusbsrvc.exe (PID 4916) - Backdoor listener on port 33001                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ **Network IOCs:**                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - C2 Server: 172.16.4.10:8080                                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - Backdoor ports: 5682, 33001                                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Persistence Mechanisms                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The malware has established persistence through:                             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - Two separate backdoor processes with network listeners                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - Multiple communication channels (ports 5682, 33001, and outbound 8080)     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ - Process names designed to appear legitimate but are not standard Windows   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ processes                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ## Recommendations                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 1. **Immediate Containment**: Isolate the compromised system from the        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ network                                                                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 2. **Process Termination**: Kill processes 1716 (license_ctrl.e) and 4916    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ (ftusbsrvc.exe)                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 3. **Network Monitoring**: Block communications to 172.16.4.10 and monitor   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ for IOCs across the network                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 4. **Forensic Imaging**: Preserve disk image for further analysis of         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ persistence mechanisms                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 5. **Incident Response**: Activate full incident response procedures for APT в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ compromise                                                                   в”Ӯ
